comments: Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a legal picking position in White's (SAS) path.
Jokic (DEN) initiates marginal contact with his off-arm at the end of the drive prior to Poeltl (SAS) absorbing the contact and making clean contact with the ball.
Poeltl (SAS) steps out of bounds.

Poeltl (SAS) wraps both arms around Jokic (DEN), who then grasps Poeltl's arm prior to receiving the pass.  The first illegal contact is the contact from Poeltl in the sequence, which is correctly called.
Johnson (SAS) legally contests Porter Jr.'s (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Poeltl's (SAS) path.
DeRozan (SAS) makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm.
Dozier (DEN) legally contests White's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
Poeltl (SAS) makes incidental foot to foot contact with Jokic (DEN) as they move off-ball. The reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a legal picking position in White's (SAS) path.
Poeltl (SAS) makes contact with the ball after it hits the backboard.
White (SAS) extends into Gordon (DEN) when he sets the screen, causing him to make contact with DeRozan (SAS).
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Murray's (SAS) path.
Poeltl (SAS) makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm/wrist on the release of his jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) makes marginal contact with White's (SAS) body at the end of the drive.
DeRozan (SAS) commits a take foul on Barton (DEN).
Barton (DEN) briefly grasps White's (SAS) arm as they move off-ball.
Barton (DEN) reaches in and the contact that occurs with White (SAS) is marginal.
Johnson (SAS) makes contact to Porter Jr.'s (DEN) arm as he catches the ball.
As Jokic (DEN) engages and disengages with Poeltl (SAS) during the rebound, incidental foot to foot contact occurs.
Porter Jr. (DEN) momentarily places a forearm on Johnson's (SAS) side during the drive but does not extend or deliver any contact.
Johnson (SAS) places an arm against Porter Jr. (DEN) and releases from contact when the two players come together.
Porter Jr. (DEN) legally contest Johnson's (SAS) driving shot attempt and makes marginal contact with Johnson's hand after the release of his shot attempt.
